@ton_blockchain @Filecoin @spacestorage We currently use Google Drive. But we are waiting for TON Storage to come out for decentralized storage.
@Filecoin @spacestorage What applications do you currently use to store your files?
The functionality of @Filecoin and the application @spacestorage are examples of what TON Storage could be like along with the applications that can be built on top of it.

In #Web3, anyone can pay for access to storage easily, and anyone can earn revenue by providing access to data storage.

The opportunity and revenue in data storage are distributed across a wider range of participants than usual. This also means it costs less to store data.

Data storage is meant to be cheap and private according to Web3’s ethos.

Clients, storage miners and retrieval miners will power Web3 data marketplaces for storage. 

Clients pay storage miners to hold their data and pay retrieval miners to get their data back.

These concentrated powers can de-platform services easily and can access data that is supposed to be private to copy and use against rivals.

This is where Web3 comes in.

Currently, most database systems are centralized within big tech firms.

Amazon, Microsoft, Google, Alibaba and Tencent control more than 70% of the cloud computing market.
